// SYNTAX TEST "source.bd" "inline mentions (guarded mid-line)"

Contact @alice about the report.
//      ^^^^^^ variable.other.mention.bd

Ping @bob and @carol, please review.
//   ^^^^ variable.other.mention.bd
//            ^^^^^^ variable.other.mention.bd

Email foo@bar.com is not a mention.
//       ^ - variable.other.mention.bd

@alice at line start
// <------ variable.other.mention.bd

Note: line-level constructs (parens-line, strings) are match-atomic by
design. Mentions inside "@alice" strings or (@alice) parens lines do
not receive a separate mention scope — the outer whole-line scope wins.
